      "narration": "Look at what your hands just learned. Point the probe along a candidate and the sum climbs. Point it across and the sum dies to zero. Point it against and the sum goes negative. One multiply and add, and it behaves like a meter with agree, ignore, and oppose on the dial. So say it plainly: the dot product is a similarity meter. Two lists of numbers go in. One honest reading of alignment comes out. And the reading tracks direction, because direction is all the sweep ever changed.",
